The '''Adler Fellowship''' is a program to support young singers managed by the [[San Francisco Opera]], started under the leadership of General Director [[Terence A. McEwen]]. The fellowship is named after [[Kurt Herbert Adler]] who managed the opera from 1953 until 1981. The fellowship comes with training and performance opportunities.<ref>[http://sfopera.com/Opera-Center/Adler-Fellows.aspx "Adler Fellowship Program", with list of Adler Fellows] on sfopera.com</ref>
==Fellows== {{Expand list|date=May 2012}} {{Div col|colwidth=20em|rules=yes}} *[[Kevin Anderson (tenor)|Kevin Anderson]] (1988) *[[Brian Asawa]] (1992) *[[Elizabeth Caballero]] (2003) *[[James Caputo]] (1993) *[[Laura Claycomb]] (1991–93) *[[Katia Escalera]] (2001) *[[Thomas G. Glenn]] (2004–05) *[[Mary Mills (soprano)|Mary Mills]] (1990–91) *[[Nadine Sierra]] (2011–2012) *[[Daniel Sumegi]] (1993–94) *[[Claudia Waite]] (1994–95) *[[Janet Williams (soprano)|Janet Williams]] (1988–89) {{Div col end}} ==References== {{Reflist}}
