{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=January 2012}} {{orphan|date=February 2012}} }}
The '''Asian Conference on Electrochemical Power Sources''' (ACEPS) is a series of scientific [[Electrochemistry|electrochemical]] power sources conferences held in [[East Asia]], [[Southeast Asia]] and [[South Asia]] at different locations. It was initiated by Professor Zempachi Ogumi in [[Japan]] in 2006; it has subsequently been held in [[China]] (2007), [[South Korea]] (2008), [[Taiwan]] (2009), [[Singapore]] (2010), [[India]] (2012), [[Japan]] (2013), and [[China]] (2015). The next meeting is to be held in [[South Korea]] in August 2017.{{Update inline|date=February 2016}}
==Background== The First Asian Conference on Electrochemical Power Sources (ACEPS-1) was held November 15–17, 2006, in [[Kyoto]], [[Japan]], with the aim of strengthening regional research potential and improving infrastructures in the Asian region. ACEPS promotes collaboration and co-operation between Asian scientists in the fields of [[fuel cell]]s, [[storage batteries]], [[super capacitor]]s and [[Electrochemistry|electrochemical]] science.
== Conferences == Up to now, seven meetings have been held: * ACEPS-1, November 15–17, 2006, [[Kyoto]], [[Japan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elech.kuic.kyoto-u.ac.jp/ACEPS/ |title=First Asian Conference on Electrochemical Power Sources |publisher=Elech.kuic.kyoto-u.ac.jp |date= |accessdate=2012-02-10 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> * ACEPS-2, October 21–23, 2007, [[Fudan University]], [[Shanghai]], [[China]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chemistry.fudan.edu.cn/aceps2/index.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070319074916/http://www.chemistry.fudan.edu.cn/aceps2/index.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2007-03-19 |title=welcome to aceps2 home page |publisher=Chemistry.fudan.edu.cn |date= |accessdate=2012-02-10 }}</ref> * ACEPS-3, November, 2008, [[Korea University]], [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]] * ACEPS-4, November 8–12, 2009, [[National Taiwan University of Science and Technology]], [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ch-e.ntust.edu.tw/front/bin/ptdetail,N12,c,7.phtml |title=NTUST - Chemical Engineering - 4th Asian Conference on Electrochemical Power Sources |publisher=Ch-e.ntust.edu.tw |date= |accessdate=2012-02-10}}</ref> * ACEPS-5, September 17–20, 2010, [[Singapore]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aceps-5.org |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622100725/http://aceps-5.org/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-06-22 |title=5th Asian Conference on Electrochemical Power Sources |publisher=ACEPS-5 |date=2010-09-20 |accessdate=2012-02-10 }}</ref> * ACEPS-6, January 5–8, 2012, [[Indian Institute of Science]] and [[Central Electro Chemical Research Institute]], [[India]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aceps.cecri.res.in/index.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120701123035/http://aceps.cecri.res.in/index.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-07-01 |title=:::ACEPS-6::: |publisher=Aceps.cecri.res.in |date= |accessdate=2012-02-10 }}</ref> * ACEPS-7, November 24–27, 2013, Co-Sponsored by Electrochemical Society of Japan and [[Chemical Society of Japan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aceps7.lhweb.jp/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130903230504/http://aceps7.lhweb.jp/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-09-03 |title=:::ACEPS-7::: |publisher=aceps7.lhweb.jp/ |date= |accessdate=2013-03-10 |df= }}</ref> * ACEPS-8, August 21–25, 2015, Co-Sponsored by [[Fudan University]], [[Shanghai]], [[China]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aceps8.allconfs.org/meeting/index_en.asp?id=2523 |title=:::ACEPS-8::: |publisher=aceps8 |date= |accessdate=2016-05-07}}</ref> * ACEPS-9, August 20–23, 2017,[[Gyeongju]], [[South Korea]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aceps9.org/ |title=:::ACEPS-9::: |publisher=aceps9 |date= |accessdate=2018-08-10}}</ref>
