{{Infobox university | name = Julius Nyerere University of Agriculture | native_name = {{nowrap|{{native phrase|sw|Chuo Kikuu cha Kilimo cha Julius Nyerere}}}} | image_name = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | established = | type = [[Public university|Public]] | affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = Dominic Kambarage | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Musoma]] | state = | province = | country = [[Tanzania]] | coor = | campus = | former_names = | free_label = | free = | colors = | colours = | athletics = | sports = | nickname = | mascot = | affiliations = | website = | logo = | footnotes = }}
The '''Julius Nyerere University of Agriculture (JNUA)''' is a proposed public university that will be built in northern [[Tanzania]]. It will be located in [[Butiama]], the hometown of [[Julius Nyerere]].This will be the country's second university dedicated to agricultural research after the [[Sokoine University of Agriculture]].<ref>{{cite news|last= |first= |date=13 April 2014 |title=Second agriculture university to honour Sokoine underway |url=http://archive.dailynews.co.tz/index.php/local-news/30297-second-agriculture-university-to-honour-sokoine-underway |archive-url=https://archive.is/20141212162946/http://archive.dailynews.co.tz/index.php/local-news/30297-second-agriculture-university-to-honour-sokoine-underway |dead-url=yes |archive-date=12 December 2014 |newspaper=Daily News |location= |accessdate=12 December 2014 }}</ref>
==History== In November 2014, the Deputy Education Minister [[Jenista Mhagama]] informed the [[National Assembly (Tanzania)|parliament]] that feasibility study is complete and her ministry has requested funding from the [[Ministry of Finance and Economic Affairs (Tanzania)|Finance Ministry]]. Apart from the main campus in Butiama, an additional four will be built in [[Serengeti District|Serengeti]], [[Bunda District|Bunda]], [[Rorya District|Rorya]] and [[Musoma District|Musoma]] districts.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=13 November 2014 |title=Feasibility study on long-awaited Butiama University now complete |url=http://www.ippmedia.com/frontend/?l=74122 |newspaper=The Guardian |location= |accessdate=12 December 2014 }}</ref>
In December 2014, President [[Jakaya Kikwete]] appointed Professor Dominic Kambarage as the inaugural Vice Chancellor of the university.<ref>{{cite news|last= |first= |date=12 December 2014 |title=Kambarage appointed Nyerere university VC |url=http://www.dailynews.co.tz/index.php/local-news/39284-kambarage-appointed-nyerere-university-vc |archive-url=https://archive.is/20141212181335/http://www.dailynews.co.tz/index.php/local-news/39284-kambarage-appointed-nyerere-university-vc |dead-url=yes |archive-date=12 December 2014 |newspaper=Daily News |location= |accessdate=12 December 2014 }}</ref>
